## 3. Target Audience & Searcher Profile

The primary searcher is an adult renter, most commonly between 25 and 40, who is either relocating to a new city, upgrading from a one-bedroom, or co-renting with a partner or roommate and needs the privacy that two full bathrooms provides. They are in the **comparison-to-decision stage** of the renter journey: they have already decided they want a 2BR/2BA and are now trying to calibrate their budget against a specific market and understand what trade-offs they will face at different price points. Their core problem is a gap between what they think a 2BR/2BA should cost and what the market actually charges, compounded by uncertainty about whether a given unit's layout actually functions for two people living independently. They expect a content format that gives them real numbers by city, explains what distinguishes one type of unit from another, and points them directly toward available inventory.

